      <h2 class="section-heading">Using a Daily Drink as Part of a Routine</h2>

      <p>
        If you choose to use a powdered drink, prepare it only as directed by the manufacturer.
        Do not exceed the recommended serving amount, and do not use a supplement as a substitute
        for a varied diet or professional health guidance.
      </p>

      <p>
        It may be useful to keep a simple routine: check the label, use the stated serving size,
        stay hydrated, and pay attention to how you personally tolerate the product.
        If you experience an unwanted reaction, discontinue use and consult a qualified professional.
      </p>

